step.reason:
\begin{align}
I &= \int x\cdot \log x\,dx\\
&= \log x \int x\,dx - \int \left[\dfrac{d}{dx}\log x \int x\,dx\right]dx\\
&= \log x \cdot \dfrac{x^2}{2} - \int \dfrac{1}{x}\cdot\dfrac{x^2}{2}\,dx\\
&= \log x \cdot \dfrac{x^2}{2} - \dfrac{1}{2}\int x\,dx = \dfrac{x^2}{2} \log x - \dfrac{x^2}{4}+ C\\
\end{align}
